Key Match Events: Yoshinobu Yamamoto had a rare poor start, allowing four runs in three innings.
Mookie Betts hit his 19th home run of the season in walk-off fashion.
Shohei Ohtani hit another home run and collected two stolen bases.
Betts and Ohtani hit back-to-back home runs to secure the win in the ninth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: The Dodgers maintained their one-game lead over the Philadelphia Phillies atop the National League standings.
The Dodgers are 14-5 when Betts hits a home run.
Shohei Ohtani is close to achieving the 60-60 club with 53 home runs and 55 stolen bases.
Others: The Dodgers will face the San Diego Padres and the Rockies again to end the 2024 campaign.
The Dodgers hope for quick recoveries for Max Muncy and Tony Gonsolin.
